How to use timeout & expected exceptions attributes in TestNG?

1.What is timeout?
According to BRD -- website should be opened in 2 seconds 
then we have use timeout -- 
Shipment should happen in 10 seconds 
more than the expected time -- then testNG will show the error
TestAttributes.testmethod1() didn't finish within the time-out 2

Time will accept milliseconds

if the page is not loaded with in the time -- TestNG will mark the testcase as failure.

2.How to use timeout?
@Test(Timeout =2000)

3.what is expected exceptions?
Not used in realtime scenario only for interview 

4.How to use excepted exceptions.

abc -- NosuchElements 
IoException -- expecting some exceptions 

@Test(exepected




